      <h1>Web App Development - Phase 1</h1>
      <p>This course is for beginners who have coded websites but are new to programming. You'll learn how to use Ruby and Rails to process forms submitted by users.</p>
      <h2>What you'll build</h2>
      <p>The possibilities just open up when you can process user submitted forms. You might choose to build an <a href="http://www.madglibs.com/">online Mad Libs game</a>, a complex <a href="http://www.wordcounter.net/">calculator</a>, a <a href="http://www.smartgirl.org/fortune.html">fortune teller</a> or even a simple   <a href="http://www.cleverbot.com/">conversational AI</a>. Click on the image below to check out an example final project (it might take up to 15 seconds to load).</p>
      <a class="thumbnail" href="http://loris-rails-1.herokuapp.com" target="_blank">
        <%= image_tag('rails_1_example.png', class: 'img-responsive') %>
      </a>
      <h2>Course structure</h2>
      <p>You'll attend weekly online video labs with one of our coaches to work on practice problems and ask questions about your final project. In between labs you'll go through tutorials to get familiar with new topics.</p>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3>Skills and concepts you'll learn</h3>
          <ul class="skill-list">
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to set up your computer for  programming in Rails</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to troubleshoot programming bugs</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to translate ideas into code</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">A basic Git workflow</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to deploy an app with Heroku</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to display an HTML page in a Rails app</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to create forms in HTML</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to use variables</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to create and access arrays</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">How to use conditional logic</li>
            <li class="skill-list-item">Common Ruby methods for strings and integers</li>
          </ul>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
